        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:02PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1102 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
south of Hindsville, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Rockhouse...                      Withrow Springs State Park...
Hindsville...                     Huntsville...
Cabanal...                        Forum...
Alabam...                         Pleasant Ridge...
Urbanette...                      Berryville...
Grandview...                      Clifty...
Oak Hill...                       Georgetown...
Eureka Springs...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
